          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Beating the Brand<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.56)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9813'>Andrew "Bee Boy" Sitte</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9813&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 19, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> With FoTR, Nazgul were a very powerful culture.  While they were vulnerable to ARV, they still had the ability to slow down the fellowship like no other culture, allowing you to win the race.  It was hard to consider moving twice when there were 2 Fierce Nazgul out, with another 1 or 2 likely on their way.<br>
<br>
Then, last weekend, all of that changed.  Many people said that Nazgul were through, and it was all because of one card.  During a tournament last weekend, I won one of my games quickly, and went to watch another.  The players were 2 of the best there, but then around site 5, one of them played 2 Flaming Brands, and the other gave up.  He was playing with Twilight Nazgul, trying to weaken Frodo and then Witch-king him, and the weaker, non-fierce Nazgul couldn&#39;t stand up to Boromir and Aragorn both with Brands.<br>
<br>
I went away thinking that Twilight Nazgul were worthless; after all, they&#39;re significantly weaker than normal Nazgul, and don&#39;t have the ability of Cantea to get rid of Brands (or more likely just avoid the characters bearing them).  However, after looking more closely at the set, it became clear why Twilight Nazgul were made so weak in combat: they&#39;re not made to win skirmishes.  If they can do significant damage before the skirmish phase, it doesn&#39;t matter if Boromir and Aragorn are both juggling 2 Brands.<br>
<br>
Sure, if I get out Twilight Witch-king and win a skirmish, I&#39;m not going to complain, but that&#39;s not their strength.  With all of the great support cards they have, they don&#39;t need to win skirmishes.  They&#39;ve got plenty of cards to corrupt Frodo before they even get to the Archery phase, and a few more if they can survive past that.<br>
<br>
The quickest way to corrupt the bearer is to force him to put on the ring.  That&#39;s what Resistance Becomes Unbearable is for.  They Will Find the Ring also works, and can help weaken other companions as well.  Once the ring is on, Wraith-world and  The Twilight World heap the burdens on the bearer.  Even before the ring goes on, It Wants to Be Found can add a few burdens.<br>
<br>
Resistance Becomes Unbearable requires you to exert a Twilight Nazgul, so it&#39;s no good if your Nazgul get ARV&#39;d.  Uruk Scout is there to prevent this.  Target Archery isn&#39;t as much of a problem.  If everything goes well, you can add a pile of burdens before the Archery phase even starts.<br>
<br>
While winning skirmishes isn&#39;t necessary, it can definitely help, especially with The Witch-king.  Striken Dumb and Ulaire Cantea could help with this, to get rid of the Brands and swords, but sticking to a theme (get the ring on and corrupting the bearer) makes it hard to find room for them, especially with how expensive they are to play.  Consider winning skirmishes a bonus, but don&#39;t count on it after the first couple sites.<br>
<br>
If your looking to avoid being corrupted by this deck or one like it, there are a number of things that can help you.  One is Sam.  Helpless can deal with Sam, but it&#39;s a condition easily dealt with through Athelas or Sleep.  Note that there are no conditions in this deck at all.  The new Frodo and Aragorn, KiE make forcing the ring on even harder.  Even better is O Elbereth, Githloniel, which can get the ring off just as fast as it&#39;s forced on.<br>
<br>
Because of these things, you have to make the most of forcing on the ring.  If you have 2 Wraith or Twilight Worlds when you force on the ring, you&#39;re adding 4-6 burdens.  It Wants to Be Found is a couple more.  If Frodo hasn&#39;t gone insane by site 9, Summit of Amon Hen should give you what you need to end it.<br>
<br>
Shadow: 35 cards<br>
3 Uruk Scout<br>
4 Resistance Becomes Unbearable<br>
3 Wraith-world<br>
3 The Twilight World<br>
3 Ulaire Attea, The Easterling<br>
3 Ulaire Enquea, Ringwraith in Twilight<br>
3 Ulaire Nelya, Ringwraith in Twilight<br>
2 The Witch-king, Lord of the Nazgul<br>
4 It Wants to be Found<br>
3 Morgul Gates<br>
3 They Will Find the Ring<br>
1 The Balrog, Durin&#39;s Bane<br>
<br>
